-- Germany Has No Leeway for More Spending, Vows to Keep Consolidation Path
-- B y   T o n y   C z u c z k a
-- 2010-11-04T12:42:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/germany-has-no-leeway-for-more-spending-vows-to-keep-consolidation-path.html
Germany’s higher estimated tax
revenue through 2012 doesn’t mean the government has leeway for
additional spending, the Finance Ministry said in an e-mailed
statement today. “On the contrary: the federal government will
resolutely stay on the path of consolidation even during the
upswing,” the statement said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
